  {
    "verifyText": {
      "id": "lf-help-content",
      "value": "This tool compares rates of return for term and whole life insurance policies for two periods: Between now and the time that you receive full cash value for your whole life policy. Between now and the time you die. After-tax returns are provided for the following: The whole life policy. The term life policy. The term life policy, with premium savings invested in a taxable account. Since whole life policy premiums are higher, the premium difference (the annual premium amount saved with a term life policy) is invested. Generally, term life insurance policy premiums are initially lower than whole life premiums, which generally are constant. Term life premiums climb, however, past the premium amount for whole life policies as you age and have to renew your term life policy."
    }
  },
